description._content: Description: Mother tree of Troodos Pine - Pinus nigra var. Karamanica, storm damaged top with seedlings underneath, in pass below Chionistra, Elevation 5,850 feet, above sea level. Location: Cyprus Date: 1920-1939 Description: Mature Troodos Pine - Pinus nigra var.Karamanica, over 300years old, showing natural reproduction in pass below Chionistra, Troodos Forest, Elevation 5,900 feet above sea level. Location: Cyprus Date: 1920-1939 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/698 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown.
